article.headline: SE Louisiana 75, Texas St. 66
article.story: HAMMOND, La. -- Patrick Sullivan tallied a double-double, and DeShawn Patterson added a career-high 21 points, leading Southeastern Louisiana in a 75-66 win over Texas State on Wednesday night. Sullivan scored 23 points, grabbed 10 boards and blocked a career-high eight shots for the Lions (13-8, 5-3 Southland Conference). Patterson, who came in averaging 4.2 points per contest, went a career-high 9 of 11 from the foul line and hit two 3-pointers. The Lions have won three straight games. Texas State led 32-29 at halftime, but the Lions went on a 13-6 run out of the break in which Sullivan scored six consecutive points and never trailed again. With the Lions up 71-66 with 21 seconds left, Sullivan and Jason Marks hit a pair of free throws apiece to seal it. Tony Bishop notched a double-double to lead the Bobcats (10-12, 4-4), scoring 19 points and grabbing 10 boards.
